title: Civic Reform Office Briefing
tags: event
on-arrival: demo_event_seen = 1

= Civic Reform Office Briefing

This is a small event. In Studio, the Object Editor lets mod authors edit this
body text, the choices below, and the result pages each choice opens.

The choices demonstrate effects. One builds volunteer support, one strengthens
the case file, and one records conflict. The status scene shows those Q
variables after the player clicks.

- @organize_volunteers: Organize volunteers.
- @review_case_file: Review the case file.
- @observe_quietly: Watch the opposition quietly.

@organize_volunteers
title: Organize volunteers.
subtitle: Effect demo: support rises.
on-arrival: demo_support += 1; demo_public_attention += 1

= Organize volunteers

Result text appears after a player clicks an option. This result raises
`demo_support`, which also unlocks the support follow-up from the starter menu.

- @demo_status: Continue

@review_case_file
title: Review the case file.
subtitle: Effect demo: case strength rises.
on-arrival: demo_case_strength += 1; demo_resources -= 1

= Review the case file

The office spends one resource to prepare evidence. Later, the complex reform
chain can read `demo_case_strength` and unlock a stronger hearing choice.

- @demo_status: Continue

@observe_quietly
title: Watch the opposition quietly.
subtitle: Effect demo: conflict rises.
on-arrival: demo_conflict += 1; demo_opposition_heat += 1

= Watch the opposition quietly

This result raises `demo_conflict`. It changes the state summary but does not
unlock the support follow-up.

- @demo_status: Continue

@demo_status
title: Demo State

= Demo State

[? if demo_support > 0 : `demo_support` is above 0, so the support line can now appear. ?]
[? if demo_conflict > 0 : `demo_conflict` is above 0, so the observation line can now appear. ?]
[? if demo_case_strength > 0 : `demo_case_strength` is above 0, so the later hearing has a better starting point. ?]

If no line appears yet, choose one of the office briefing options first.

- @root: Back to start

@support_followup
title: Follow up on support
view-if: demo_support > 0

= Follow up on support

This section is hidden until `demo_support` is above 0. In Studio, conditions
like this appear as `view-if` or requirements. They explain why some player
choices are not visible at the start.

- @root: Back to start
